Example 1: a method that returns the sum of two integers 

# Informal Pseudo-Code

Prompt the user to enter an integer. 
Save the input to a variable.
Check that the input is an integer.
- If so, move on. If not, prompt the user again to enter an integer. 

Repeat above steps for the second integer. 

Assign the value of adding the two integers to a variable.
Output that variable. 


# Formal Psuedo-Code

START

PRINT "Enter the first integer you'd like to add."
GET number from user.
SET number1 = input from user
WHILE number1 != integer
  PRINT "Enter an integer."
  GET number from user. 
  SET number1 = input from userWHILE number1 != integer
  PRINT "Enter an integer."
  GET number from user.
  SET number1 = input from user

PRINT "Enter the second integer you'd like to add."
GET number from user.
SET number2 = input from user
WHILE number1 != integer
  PRINT "Enter an integer."
  GET number from user.
  SET number1 = input from user

SET result = number1 + number2
PRINT result

END
